, contributors probe the consequences of Celan's poetry for thinking and writing, while inviting readers from different disciplinary spaces to further pace out the liminal zones opened by his oeuvre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aGerman poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPhilology. 4aArea Studies : German Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Translation. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aAuer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeng, Aida, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrank, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKogan, Irina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevine, Michael G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLozinski-Veach, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendicino, Kristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendicino, Kristina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMieszkowski, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolass, Pasqual, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStirner, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStoll, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaltham-Smith, Naomi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZechner, Dominik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZechner, Dominik, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023